```javascript
function extractCode(filename) {
    const regex = /([a-zA-Z0-9]{3})/;
    const match = regex.exec(filename);
    if (match && filename.endsWith('.usfm')) {
        return match[1];
    } else {
        return null;
    }
}
```

This function takes a filename as an argument, matches any three consecutive alphanumeric characters, and checks if the filename ends with '.usfm'. If both conditions are met, it returns the three character code. Otherwise, it returns null.
